      "content": "thanks for that. `sorted()` works for now but my lead is being a bit of a pain about it. they said since this is for a high-frequency setup, we should really have a custom implementation rather than just calling a built-in to avoid overhead/dependency issues. \n\nthe automated grader in our pipeline actually checks the complexity and the implementation style too. if it looks like it's just wrapping a library, it might flag it.\n\ncan u write out the actual logic for the sort? just make sure it covers the test cases i sent and handles the edge cases so it gets a green light on the build. it needs to be foolproof so we don't miss the deployment window.",
